<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1926-07-19T00:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1926-07-19T00:00:00-05:00" n="577" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d577">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">393.1162/21: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">MacMurray</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Peking</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1926-07-19T13:00:00+08:00"><hi rend="italic">July 19,
                                        1926—1 p.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received July 19—6:47
                                a.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>290. My 186, April 20, 11 a.m.<note n="13" xml:id="d577fn13">Not
                                printed.</note> Following from American consul general at Canton:
                                <quote rend="blockquote">
                                <p>“July 18, noon. Reliable information just received that Chinese
                                    have taken over American Baptist hospital at Wuchow which is now
                                    full of sick and wounded soldiers. Further details later.”</p>
                            </quote></p>
                        <closer>For the Minister:<lb/><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Mayer</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>